OL,3,CSouthport attacker's father called him
OL,4,C'good boy' after school knife incident
OL,6,FMr McGarry said he had been giving an
OL,7,Fassembly in the hall when he saw AR
OL,8,Fwho ran off "very quickly".
OL,10,FThe headteacher said he followed the
OL,11,Fteenager down the corridor and was a
OL,12,Ffew yards behind him when he saw a
OL,13,Fgroup of students coming towards them.
OL,15,F"That was the point where he produced
OL,16,Fthis hockey stick out from underneath
OL,17,Fthe puffa jacket he had on," he said.
OL,19,F"He raised the hockey stick back as if
OL,20,Fhe was going to swipe it towards these
OL,21,Fstudents. It hit another student."
